# Healthy Food - API Documentation & Postman Guide

This document provides a complete list of backend API endpoints, including how to use filters, sorting, and how to test them using Postman.

## 🚀 Postman Setup Instructions

1.  **Base URL**: `http://localhost:5001/api`
2.  **Authentication**:
    -   For protected routes, go to the **Headers** tab in Postman.
    -   Add a new key: `Authorization`.
    -   Value: `Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN`.
    -   *(Tip: You can use `dev_token_bypass` as a token for local development testing).*
3.  **Content-Type**: For `POST` and `PUT` requests (except file uploads), set `Content-Type: application/json` in the Headers.
4.  **File Uploads**: Use `form-data` in the **Body** tab. Select `File` type for image fields (e.g., `product_image_file`).

---

## 📂 Product API (`/api/products`)

### **GET /** - List All Products
Used for the shop page. Supports advanced filtering and sorting.

**Query Parameters:**
- `search`: Filter by product name (e.g., `?search=apple`).
- `category`: Filter by Category ID (e.g., `?category=2`).
- `brand`: Filter by brand name.
- `minPrice` / `maxPrice`: Filter by price range.
- `rating`: Filter by minimum rating (e.g., `?rating=4`).
- `page`: Pagination page number (default: 1).
- `limit`: Products per page (default: 12).
- `sort`: Sorting options:
    - `price_asc`: Lowest price first.
    - `price_desc`: Highest price first.
    - `rating`: Best rated first.
    - `newest`: Most recently added.
    - `discount`: Highest discount first.

---

## 📂 Admin & Category API (`/api/admin`)

### **GET /categories**
Supports basic filtering for the admin panel.
- `category_name`: Filter by name.
- `status`: `1` for Active, `0` for Inactive.
- `parent_id`: Filter by parent category.

### **GET /users** (Protected)
Requires `Superadmin` or [Admin](file:///c:/healthyfood/HealthyFood/admin-frontend/admin-frontend/src/views/admin/admin-management/AdminManagement.jsx#15-195). Returns all registered users.

### **PUT /update-role** (Protected)
Requires `Superadmin` or [Admin](file:///c:/healthyfood/HealthyFood/admin-frontend/admin-frontend/src/views/admin/admin-management/AdminManagement.jsx#15-195).
- **Body**: `{"id": 10, "role_id": 2}`

### **GET /roles** (Protected)
Returns the list of all available roles (ID and Name).

---

## 📂 Authentication API (`/api/auth`)

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Body Example |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `POST` | `/auth/send-otp` | Send OTP to phone | `{"phone": "1234567890"}` |
| `POST` | `/auth/verify-otp` | Verify and Login | `{"phone": "1234567890", "otp": "123456"}` |
| `POST` | `/auth/login` | Email Login | `{"email": "admin@test.com", "password": "..."}`|
| `POST` | `/auth/register` | Register User | `{"name": "...", "email": "...", "password": "..."}` |

---

## 🛠️ Sorting & Filtering Quick Reference

| Feature | Param | Values |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Search** | `search` | String (any text) |
| **Sort Price** | `sort` | `price_asc`, `price_desc` |
| **Sort New** | `sort` | `newest` |
| **Filter Stock**| (N/A) | Managed via Stock column logic |
| **Pagination**| `page`, `limit` | Numbers |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Always ensure the backend server is running (`node app.js`) before testing in Postman.
